WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:50.200 --> 00:52.350
Pretty nice up here, isn't it?

00:52.440 --> 00:54.351
- Kermit?
- Huh?

00:54.440 --> 00:57.159
What if we drift out to sea?

00:57.240 --> 01:00.869
What if we're never heard from again?
What if there's a storm?

01:00.960 --> 01:04.953
- Or we get struck by lightning?
- That'd be neat.

01:05.040 --> 01:08.794
Listen, nothing's gonna happen.
This is just the opening credits.

01:08.880 --> 01:11.553
Oh. Where are they?

01:12.560 --> 01:14.551
Wow!

01:14.640 --> 01:19.031
- <i>"The Great Muppet Caper."</i>
- Nice title.

01:19.880 --> 01:21.108
Whoo-wee!

01:21.200 --> 01:23.794
I'd like to try this without the balloon.

01:23.880 --> 01:26.758
- Try what? Plummeting?
- Yeah!

01:26.840 --> 01:29.593
I suppose you could try it once.

01:29.680 --> 01:31.636
- Kermit?
- Mm?

01:31.720 --> 01:34.280
How long are these opening credits?

01:34.360 --> 01:37.158
Just about another minute or so.

01:37.240 --> 01:39.231
My ears are popping.

01:40.120 --> 01:43.476
I wonder how far you
could plummet before you blacked out.

01:43.560 --> 01:46.757
Well, don't try it, Gonzo.
We need you for this movie.

01:46.840 --> 01:49.354
Sure is tempting.

01:53.000 --> 01:54.035
- Kermit?
- Huh?

01:54.120 --> 01:56.998
What does "BSC" stand for?

01:57.080 --> 01:59.594
I don't know.

02:03.480 --> 02:06.677
Gee, a lot of people worked on this movie.

02:06.760 --> 02:10.229
This is nothing.
Wait till you see the end credits.

02:18.320 --> 02:19.639
- Kermit?
- Mm?

02:19.720 --> 02:22.678
- Are the credits over?
- Not quite.

02:25.120 --> 02:27.190
Nobody reads those names
anyway, do they?

02:27.280 --> 02:30.511
Sure. They all have families.

02:30.600 --> 02:31.555
Ah.

02:31.640 --> 02:33.835
That's it. The sky is clear.

02:33.920 --> 02:37.754
So, OK. Well, now what do we do?
I mean, how does this movie start?

02:37.840 --> 02:41.071
- Well, we just pull that rope.
- Yes, sir!

02:44.960 --> 02:47.952
We're going down!

02:48.040 --> 02:50.349
Heads up, below!

03:02.600 --> 03:05.194
What a fantastic beginning.

03:07.560 --> 03:10.632
<i>There'll be spectacle</i>
<i>There'll be fantasy</i>

03:10.720 --> 03:14.190
<i>There'll be derring-do</i>
<i>and stuff like you have never seen</i>

03:14.280 --> 03:17.636
- <i>Hey. A movie</i>
- <i>Yeah. We're gonna be a movie</i>

03:17.720 --> 03:20.678
- <i>Starring everybody</i>
- <i>And me</i>

03:20.760 --> 03:24.196
<i>There'll be heroes bold</i>
<i>There'll be comedy</i>

03:24.280 --> 03:27.511
<i>And a lot of fuss</i>
<i>that ends for us real happily</i>

03:27.600 --> 03:31.036
- <i>Hey. A movie</i>
- <i>We can watch it all develop</i>

03:31.120 --> 03:34.112
- <i>Starring everybody</i>
- <i>And me</i>

03:34.200 --> 03:37.556
<i>We'll take the world</i>
<i>and set it on its ear</i>

03:37.640 --> 03:41.758
<i>Come on. Join in</i>
<i>We're gonna start right here</i>

03:45.840 --> 03:47.910
It's OK. I landed on my head.

03:48.000 --> 03:49.991
Come on!

03:50.080 --> 03:51.672
Here, chicken!

03:51.760 --> 03:54.991
Hey! Why, you...

03:55.080 --> 03:56.638
Whoa!

03:56.720 --> 04:00.190
Hold it!

04:00.280 --> 04:03.352
- Go ahead, Kermit.
- Thank you. See, in this film,

04:03.440 --> 04:07.035
me and Fozzie play crack investigative
reporters for <i>The Daily Chronicle.</i>

04:07.120 --> 04:10.192
And Gonzo, he's our photographer.
And it's gonna be terrific.

04:12.560 --> 04:15.393
Boy, I wish I were you people,
seeing this for the first time.

04:15.480 --> 04:17.516
Wh?

04:19.399 --> 04:22.517
- <i>There'll be crooks and cops</i>
- <i>There'll be villainy</i>

04:22.600 --> 04:25.797
<i>But with us on call</i>
<i>we'll fix it all real easily</i>

04:25.880 --> 04:29.509
- <i>Hey. A movie</i>
- <i>Wow. It's gonna be terrific</i>

04:29.600 --> 04:32.990
- <i>Starring everybody</i>
- And me.

04:33.080 --> 04:35.150
Argh!

04:36.200 --> 04:38.555
Now, what we need, guys,
is an exciting photo story.

04:38.640 --> 04:42.553
Right this way, young lady.
I'll take a picture of this chicken.

04:43.640 --> 04:45.392
- Beautiful.
- That's great, Gonzo.

04:45.480 --> 04:48.074
Yeah. Smile, chicky babe.

04:53.920 --> 04:56.957
My jewels! That man stole my jewels!

04:57.040 --> 04:59.429
Help! My jewels!

05:07.800 --> 05:11.270
Look up. Hey, do you wanna
make the front pages or not?

05:11.360 --> 05:13.237
Kermit, I got a great picture of the chicken.

05:13.320 --> 05:14.150
Oh, good.

05:14.240 --> 05:17.630
<i>There'll be mystery and catastrophe</i>

05:17.720 --> 05:21.156
<i>But it's all in fun</i>
<i>You paid the money. Wait and see</i>

05:21.240 --> 05:24.835
- <i>Hey. A movie</i>
- <i>Is there any way to stop it?</i>

05:24.920 --> 05:28.469
- <i>Starring everybody</i>
- <i>Everybody</i>

05:28.560 --> 05:31.393
- <i>Everybody and</i>
- <i>Oh...</i>

05:35.120 --> 05:37.270
<i>Me</i>

05:43.280 --> 05:46.352
How could you miss a story like that?

05:47.280 --> 05:50.397
It was right under your noses,
practically bit you on the seat of the pants.

05:50.480 --> 05:51.799
There's just no excuse.

05:51.880 --> 05:54.952
I guess this would be the wrong time
to ask for a raise?

05:55.400 --> 05:58.073
Raise? A raise?

05:59.040 --> 06:01.395
I'll give you a raise!

06:02.440 --> 06:05.159
Did you read these headlines? Huh?

06:05.240 --> 06:09.028
"Jewel heist on Main Street."
And it's nice bold print, isn't it?

06:09.120 --> 06:11.111
- Yes, it's very easy to read.
- Mm.

06:11.920 --> 06:13.956
- Shut up now.
- Sorry.

06:14.040 --> 06:17.191
"Lady Holiday's Jewels Stolen",
that's what it says in the <i>Times.</i>

06:17.280 --> 06:22.400
And here's the <i>Herald.</i>
"Fashion Queen of London Robbed."

06:22.480 --> 06:25.438
And last but not least...

06:26.320 --> 06:28.914
...here's our cute little banner story.

06:29.000 --> 06:31.912
"Identical Twins Join the <i>Chronicle</i> Staff."

06:32.000 --> 06:34.468
Now, I ask you,
what paper would you buy?

06:35.200 --> 06:37.873
- I read the one that has "Dear Abby".
- Bah!

06:42.160 --> 06:45.357
Gee, Mr Tarkanian. We thought identical
twins working on a newspaper

06:45.440 --> 06:47.829
- would make an interesting story.
- Yeah.

06:47.920 --> 06:53.313
Well, it doesn't. Especially since
you two guys don't look anything alike.

06:53.400 --> 06:56.278
Well, that's cos Fozzie's not wearing
his hat. Fozzie, put your hat back on.

06:56.360 --> 06:59.432
Oh. Yes, sir. See?

07:00.040 --> 07:02.190
Oh, yeah.

07:02.280 --> 07:05.909
I can see it now. But that's still
no excuse for blowing a story.

07:06.000 --> 07:09.834
- We'll do better next time.
- Next time? Next time?

07:09.920 --> 07:12.150
What makes you think
there's gonna be a next time?

07:12.240 --> 07:14.435
Well, if there isn't
it's gonna be a real short movie.

07:14.520 --> 07:16.112
Look, the only reason I hired you two jerks

07:16.200 --> 07:19.033
was because your old man
was a friend of mine.

07:19.600 --> 07:21.431
Dad spoke well of you too.

07:21.520 --> 07:25.672
Well, I'm as sentimental as the next guy.
That's why I don't want him to hear this.

07:25.760 --> 07:28.035
You're fired.

07:28.120 --> 07:31.715
- Take that thing down off the ceiling.
- Yeah, but, Mr Tarkanian...

07:31.800 --> 07:34.439
- Gonzo.
- Check. Whoo-wee!

07:34.520 --> 07:35.919
Won't you listen to reason, sir?

07:36.000 --> 07:39.072
I'm not listening to anything
and I'm not giving you your job back.

07:39.160 --> 07:41.879
I don't want you to give us anything.
We just want to go to England

07:41.960 --> 07:44.190
and talk to Lady Holiday -
the woman who was robbed?

07:44.280 --> 07:46.316
And we'll catch those jewel thieves for you.

07:46.400 --> 07:48.709
You see, all you have to do
is pay our way to London.

07:48.800 --> 07:49.630
Oh!

07:49.720 --> 07:52.473
Is that all I have to do?

07:52.560 --> 07:54.596
Well, we could use
some new luggage for the trip.

07:54.680 --> 07:56.318
Luggage?

07:56.400 --> 07:59.949
- Now look, beat it. I got a deadline to meet.
- But how are we gonna get to London?

08:00.040 --> 08:04.397
I'll tell you what, Fozzie, since you're such
an investigative reporter, you figure it out.

08:04.480 --> 08:08.598
- I'm Fozzie.
- Oh, yeah, yeah. The hat.

08:11.840 --> 08:14.752
Stop the presses!

08:15.480 --> 08:17.277
Why? What happened?

08:17.360 --> 08:19.874
I don't know.
I've always wanted to say that.

08:19.960 --> 08:22.190
Look, you guys...

08:36.159 --> 08:39.197
Oh, boy.
It must be 50 below in here.

08:39.280 --> 08:41.236
You're lucky, you have fur.

08:41.320 --> 08:46.997
No, no, no. You're the one with the fur.
Turn on your light and see for yourself.

08:47.080 --> 08:48.672
Oh, yeah!

08:48.760 --> 08:50.796
I keep mixing us up.

08:51.760 --> 08:54.957
I think I'll read for a while.

08:55.920 --> 08:58.798
- I wish I had a book.
- Hey, Kermit?

08:58.880 --> 09:01.758
Can you reach the hostess call button?
I'm hungry.

09:01.840 --> 09:04.434
They don't serve food in ninth class.

09:04.520 --> 09:07.751
What?
$12 and you don't even get a meal?

09:08.200 --> 09:13.399
Hey, could you guys keep it down?
I'm trying to watch the movie.

09:14.280 --> 09:17.477
- Hey, somebody's coming.
- Maybe they're bringing hamburgers.

09:17.560 --> 09:20.950
- All out for England!
- Oh, great, the plane is landing.

09:21.040 --> 09:25.238
- The plane? Nah, the plane lands in Italy.
- Huh?

09:25.320 --> 09:27.788
- You land in England.
- Whoa!

09:28.840 --> 09:31.035
Kermmmmiiitt!

09:33.200 --> 09:35.111
What's happening?

09:35.200 --> 09:37.919
Whoopee!

09:41.080 --> 09:43.878
Geronimo!

09:49.760 --> 09:52.228
Glug!

09:52.320 --> 09:54.356
For once the forecast was right.

09:54.440 --> 09:57.113
It said it was going to rain cats and dogs.

09:57.200 --> 10:00.431
- No, no. We're bears and frogs.
- And Gonzos.

10:00.520 --> 10:04.115
Whatever you are, whoever you are,
welcome to Great Britain.

10:04.200 --> 10:06.395
Great Britain?
We're actually in Great Britain!

10:06.480 --> 10:09.631
Oh, no, we'll never get to England now.

10:09.720 --> 10:12.439
You are in England, my furry friend.

10:12.520 --> 10:16.035
This 'sceptred isle.
This jewel of the North Atlantic.

10:16.120 --> 10:17.917
Oh, good. Well, we're going to London

10:18.000 --> 10:20.673
and we were wondering
if you could recommend a nice hotel.

10:20.760 --> 10:23.433
- Actually, a cheap hotel.
- How cheap?

10:23.960 --> 10:28.988
- Free.
- That narrows the field a bit. Let's see.

10:29.080 --> 10:32.197
"Places where you can park
your carcasses."

10:32.280 --> 10:34.555
Bus terminals. River banks.

10:34.640 --> 10:38.269
- The Happiness Hotel.
- Happiness Hotel? That sounds great.

10:38.360 --> 10:41.591
What's wrong with bus terminals?

10:41.680 --> 10:43.875
Well, thanks a lot for your help, sir.

10:52.560 --> 10:54.073
Hey, guys, this is London.

10:54.160 --> 10:56.879
Yeah, London!
We made it! Oh, boy!

10:56.960 --> 10:58.757
- Is that the Eiffel Tower?
- Yeah!

10:58.840 --> 11:00.831
- No.
- No, no.

11:01.720 --> 11:03.312
- Hey, Kermit?
- Yeah?

11:03.400 --> 11:06.358
- Are bears allowed in those fountains?
- What?

11:06.440 --> 11:08.158
Are bears allowed in those fountains?

11:08.240 --> 11:10.151
- No, I don't think so.
- I need a bath.

11:11.320 --> 11:15.359
This is terrific.
Wow, look at the scenery.

11:15.440 --> 11:19.069
It's very realistic.
Hey, what's the name of this river?

11:19.160 --> 11:22.072
- I don't know.
- I think it's the English River.

11:22.160 --> 11:23.434
Oh.

11:23.520 --> 11:26.751
I'll take a picture of it.
Say cheese!

11:27.720 --> 11:29.199
Did I get my elbow in the shot?

11:29.280 --> 11:32.556
- Don't worry. It adds human interest.
- But I'm a bear.

11:32.640 --> 11:35.473
- Anyone for the Happiness Hotel?
- Huh?

11:35.560 --> 11:37.516
- Oh, Happiness Hotel!
- That's us!

11:37.600 --> 11:40.034
- Yes, we want the Happiness Hotel.
- Yeah.

11:42.360 --> 11:43.998
Argh!

11:45.480 --> 11:48.074
Wow.

11:48.160 --> 11:50.674
Boy, another crash landing.
That was terrible.

11:50.760 --> 11:52.990
Well, we'll just have to do it again.

11:53.080 --> 11:57.471
Oh, look. The Happiness Hotel.
What do you think, guys?

11:57.560 --> 11:58.515
Wow.

11:58.600 --> 12:02.991
If that's the Happiness Hotel
I'd hate to see what the sad one looks like.

12:16.880 --> 12:19.519
- Excuse me?
- What?

12:19.600 --> 12:21.909
We'd like a room.

12:22.000 --> 12:23.911
Really?

12:24.000 --> 12:26.639
Yeah, we'd like to check in.

12:26.720 --> 12:29.951
Somebody's checking in!

12:30.040 --> 12:32.429
Somebody's checking in?

12:34.480 --> 12:38.439
<i>Oh. There's no fire in the fireplace</i>
<i>There's no carpet on the floor</i>

12:38.520 --> 12:41.956
<i>Don't try to order dinner</i>
<i>There's no kitchen any more</i>

12:42.040 --> 12:45.237
<i>But if the road's been kinda bumpy</i>
<i>and you need to rest a spell</i>

12:45.320 --> 12:48.551
<i>Well. Welcome home</i>
<i>to the Happiness Hotel</i>

12:53.840 --> 12:57.150
- Hey, how are you guys fixing to pay?
- What are our choices?

12:57.240 --> 13:00.232
A, credit card. B, cash.

13:00.320 --> 13:02.880
C, sneak out in the middle of the night.

13:03.480 --> 13:05.038
We'll take C.

13:05.120 --> 13:07.759
Very popular choice.

13:10.520 --> 13:14.149
<i>If you got luggage keep it handy</i>
<i>but you're running out of luck</i>

13:14.240 --> 13:17.789
<i>Cos the bellhops ain't too organised</i>
<i>and the elevator's stuck</i>

13:17.880 --> 13:20.838
<i>Still if you don't mind friendly animals</i>
<i>and can learn to stand the smell</i>

13:20.920 --> 13:24.549
<i>Well. Welcome home</i>
<i>to the Happiness Hotel</i>

13:30.560 --> 13:33.074
You know, I may be mistaken,
but the bellhops look like rats.

13:33.160 --> 13:35.435
You should see the chambermaids.

13:47.080 --> 13:48.718
- <i>Welcome home</i>
- <i>Welcome home</i>

13:48.960 --> 13:50.791
- <i>Welcome home</i>
- <i>Welcome home</i>

13:50.880 --> 13:54.111
<i>No matter where you wander</i>
<i>you will never do as well</i>

13:59.200 --> 14:02.795
<i>OK. The lobby's looking shabby</i>
<i>and it's got the wrong address</i>

14:02.880 --> 14:06.236
<i>And the whole dang thing has</i>
<i>been condemned by American Express</i>

14:06.320 --> 14:09.517
<i>Still the management is cheerful</i>
<i>though the whole joint's gone to hell</i>

14:09.600 --> 14:13.991
<i>Well. Welcome home</i>
<i>to the Happiness Hotel</i>

14:14.640 --> 14:17.234
- You guys live here?
- Yeah, but only between gigs.

14:17.320 --> 14:20.710
So that means we've been here this time,
what, five years?

14:20.800 --> 14:24.952
Yeah, but, like, OK, you know, our agent,
you know, like, he says, I mean, like,

14:25.040 --> 14:28.555
things are really going to break
as soon as we get our new glossies.

14:29.080 --> 14:31.196
Argh!

14:31.280 --> 14:33.316
What's wrong with the drummer?
He looks a little crazed.

14:33.400 --> 14:37.075
Aw, he's just upset about missing the
Rembrandt exhibit at the National Gallery.

14:37.160 --> 14:39.628
Renoir!

15:16.080 --> 15:17.798
- <i>Oh. There are bugs</i>
- <i>There are bugs</i>

15:17.880 --> 15:19.836
- <i>And there are lice</i>
- <i>There are lice</i>

15:19.920 --> 15:23.356
Sure, we have our little problems
but you'll never beat the price

15:23.440 --> 15:26.796
- <i>You got every kind of critter</i>
- <i>You got every kind of pest</i>

15:26.880 --> 15:30.395
But we treat 'em all as equals
just like any other guest

15:30.480 --> 15:33.631
Though you're cleaner than the others
still, as far as we can tell

15:33.720 --> 15:36.792
You'll fit right in to the Happiness Hotel

15:36.880 --> 15:42.352
We'll fit right in to the Happiness Hotel

15:42.440 --> 15:45.193
Say cheese!

15:48.800 --> 15:51.394
You are all weirdos.

15:52.320 --> 15:53.275
Ugh.

15:54.400 --> 15:56.516
Oh, that's just fine right there.

15:58.800 --> 16:00.836
Thank you.

16:01.800 --> 16:04.360
Hey, not bad.

16:04.440 --> 16:07.238
Are you sure we can afford this?

16:07.320 --> 16:09.311
Hey, Kermit, I'm getting hungry.

16:09.400 --> 16:11.595
- Call room service.
- There's no phone.

16:11.680 --> 16:15.514
- That's OK. There's no food either.
- Come on, Rizzo.

16:15.600 --> 16:18.273
Look, why don't we forget about food
and get a good night's sleep?

16:18.360 --> 16:21.909
We have to get up early
to interview Lady Holiday.

16:22.000 --> 16:26.232
Boy, I sure could use something
from one or more of the basic food groups.

16:26.720 --> 16:30.395
We'll have breakfast in the morning.
Right now, let's just be thankful we're here.

16:33.920 --> 16:35.353
Say, this is nice.

16:35.440 --> 16:37.795
Can somebody
turn out the light?

16:38.800 --> 16:39.471
Thank you.

16:42.200 --> 16:47.479
This is Lady Holiday.
Milan speaking? Then put him on.

16:47.560 --> 16:49.869
Oh, yes, darling. Yes, I'm fine.

16:49.960 --> 16:53.509
I had quite a scare.
Thank God I wasn't hurt.

16:53.600 --> 16:58.355
Of course my diamonds were valuable.
All my diamonds are valuable.

16:58.440 --> 17:00.749
Now, darling, I want you
to call the United States and tell <i>Vogue</i>

17:00.840 --> 17:03.354
they can't have the photographs
of the spring line until after the show.

17:03.440 --> 17:09.196
I'm not too happy with some of the designs.
Still have to make some changes.

17:14.960 --> 17:18.839
Well, I'm looking at three of the gowns now
and I can see horrendous mistakes.

17:18.920 --> 17:21.275
Of course Paris should be notified.

17:21.359 --> 17:24.636
Carla. The neckline on that gown
is too high, don't you think?

17:24.720 --> 17:26.915
- I rather like the effect.
- Do you like looking like an ostrich?

17:27.000 --> 17:29.116
- Of course not.
- And Marla.

17:29.200 --> 17:30.918
Too many frills and furbelows.

17:31.000 --> 17:34.231
I don't think we should strive
for the fantail pigeon look, do you?

17:34.320 --> 17:37.869
And you, Darla. That outfit's the pits.

17:37.960 --> 17:39.951
Loose where it should be tight
and tight where it should be loose,

17:40.040 --> 17:41.234
like the folds on a turkey's neck.

17:41.320 --> 17:45.916
Why would I design
such atrocious-looking clothes? Oh!

17:46.000 --> 17:49.276
- I must be getting senile.
- <i>Yes. Lady Holiday?</i>

17:49.360 --> 17:52.238
We have to make drastic changes
in the new line before the show tomorrow.

17:52.320 --> 17:56.313
All my girls are going around
looking like barnyard animals.

17:58.600 --> 18:01.160
Good heavens. Who are you?

18:04.320 --> 18:10.236
My name is Miss Piggy and
I would like to be a high-fashion model.

18:11.240 --> 18:14.391
Doesn't surprise me.
Seems to be the way we're heading.

18:14.480 --> 18:18.314
I've always dreamed
of being a Holiday model.

18:18.400 --> 18:22.313
I have brought my <i>je ne sais quoi</i> and
my portfolio all the way here to London

18:22.400 --> 18:26.598
to see you, the one and only Lady Holiday.

18:27.840 --> 18:30.354
- May I come in?
- Absolutely not.

18:31.400 --> 18:33.391
- May I show you my portfolio?
- No.

18:33.480 --> 18:36.836
Good. Here. You may open it.

18:37.280 --> 18:37.917
Ah.

18:38.000 --> 18:41.197
This is me reeking grandeur.

18:41.280 --> 18:43.953
Being aloof.

18:44.040 --> 18:46.600
Being demure. Ah.

18:46.680 --> 18:48.352
Daring.

18:48.440 --> 18:52.035
- Interesting range of emotions.
- You think so?

18:52.120 --> 18:56.557
Well, as you can see from
this small sampling, modelling is my life.

18:56.640 --> 18:59.313
It is my destiny. I shall accept nothing less.

18:59.400 --> 19:02.870
I can offer you a job as a receptionist.

19:02.960 --> 19:06.748
I'll take it! I'll take it!
Oh, thank you, thank you! Thank you!

19:06.840 --> 19:08.478
Oh! Oh! Oh!

19:08.560 --> 19:13.588
You won't be sorry, I promise. I can type,
I can take shorthand, I can make coffee.

19:13.680 --> 19:16.638
- I can do it all.
- Sit.

19:16.720 --> 19:20.315
- I can sit. I'm very good at sitting.
- Are you quite under control?

19:20.400 --> 19:22.755
Mm, mm, mm, mm!

19:23.480 --> 19:25.994
Now, I'll be lunching with my brother Nicky.

19:26.080 --> 19:29.436
He's second in command here
and he's an irresponsible parasite.

19:29.520 --> 19:31.192
But I had to bring him into the business

19:31.280 --> 19:33.236
because he squandered
his half of the inheritance

19:33.320 --> 19:36.790
and he has categorically no prospects.
Not that he's grateful.

19:36.880 --> 19:39.838
He still gambles and incurs bad debts,
uses my charge accounts,

19:39.920 --> 19:43.595
eats my food and borrows my cars
without asking permission.

19:43.680 --> 19:46.194
And certainly he's not to be trusted.

19:46.280 --> 19:49.511
I wouldn't even put it past him to try to steal
my most valuable and largest jewel,

19:49.600 --> 19:51.750
the fabulous Baseball Diamond.

19:51.840 --> 19:56.072
And I don't know why his bow ties
are always crooked.

19:56.160 --> 20:00.312
- Still, in all, he is my brother.
- Why are you telling me all this?

20:00.400 --> 20:02.356
It's plot exposition. It has to go somewhere.

20:02.440 --> 20:05.477
Anyway, I want you
to answer the telephone while I'm gone

20:05.560 --> 20:07.676
and straighten up the office.

20:07.760 --> 20:09.716
Consider it done.

20:10.640 --> 20:13.359
Everything's under control. Not to sweat.

20:14.320 --> 20:17.278
Carry on. I'll be back in an hour.

20:18.720 --> 20:19.630
Whee!

20:19.720 --> 20:21.836
Oh, boy, oh, boy, oh, boy, oh, boy!

20:21.920 --> 20:25.595
Oh, I am going to be a famous model.
Oh, I'm so happy for me.

20:25.680 --> 20:29.559
Miss Piggy, you are on your way.

20:29.640 --> 20:32.359
Where does Lady Holiday get off
calling me an ostrich?

20:32.440 --> 20:35.796
We'll get even with Lady Holiday tonight
when we steal her necklace.

20:35.880 --> 20:39.395
What are you going to wear
for the robbery?

20:40.240 --> 20:41.434
Hi.

20:41.520 --> 20:45.308
- Hi. Hello.
- Hubba hubba!

20:45.400 --> 20:47.755
Excuse me, where's Lady Holiday's office?

20:47.840 --> 20:50.195
- Round the corner, to the left.
- Oh. Thank you.

20:50.280 --> 20:52.874
- Did you just give directions to a frog?
- I guess I did.

20:52.960 --> 20:55.520
Smile.

20:55.600 --> 20:57.670
Is that a new photographer?

20:57.760 --> 20:59.512
Urgh!

21:00.800 --> 21:04.236
- I think I'm stuck.
- Gonzo? Gonzo!

21:04.320 --> 21:06.276
Gonzo. Gonzo.

21:06.360 --> 21:08.351
Pull.

21:10.640 --> 21:14.599
- Gonzo, are you OK?
- Oh, sure. It was just my nose.

21:14.680 --> 21:17.274
Hey, you guys stay here.
I'll find Lady Holiday.

21:17.360 --> 21:17.951
Yes, sir.

21:18.040 --> 21:22.795
Hey, Fozzie. Come on,
get your nose in here. It's really fun.

21:27.840 --> 21:30.832
Mr Holiday? Did you order
a gross of flowered socks?

21:31.240 --> 21:34.596
Oh! What an honour.
You're all so wonderful.

21:34.680 --> 21:38.309
Thank you for choosing <i>moi</i>
as model of the year.

21:38.400 --> 21:42.439
Oh! I never dreamed
when I first began in this business

21:42.520 --> 21:45.080
that I would reach such lofty heights.

21:45.160 --> 21:47.355
Thank you! Thank you!

21:47.440 --> 21:49.715
Excuse me.

21:51.680 --> 21:54.240
So, what do you think
about the drapes, hm?

21:54.320 --> 21:56.959
Personally, I'd rather see shutters. Yes.

21:57.440 --> 21:59.749
And on this wall here...

22:13.200 --> 22:15.430
Lady Holiday?

22:17.200 --> 22:19.316
Lady Holiday?

22:30.840 --> 22:32.831
Gee, are you OK?

22:32.920 --> 22:36.230
I don't think I'll ever be the same.

22:36.320 --> 22:38.754
- Pardon?
- Oh.

22:38.840 --> 22:41.274
I mean, I don't usually fall like that.

22:41.360 --> 22:44.875
I thought it was a very nice fall.
It was quite graceful, actually.

22:44.960 --> 22:48.350
Oh, thank you, whoever you are.

22:48.440 --> 22:50.431
My name is Kermit the Frog

22:50.520 --> 22:54.638
and I've come all the way from America
to interview you for <i>The Daily Chronicle.</i>

22:54.720 --> 22:56.870
Me? Why me?

22:56.960 --> 22:58.951
Because you're Lady Holiday.

23:00.480 --> 23:01.913
Oh. Oh.

23:02.000 --> 23:04.719
Yeah, right. Reason enough.

23:04.800 --> 23:06.552
Um...

23:06.640 --> 23:08.198
You wanna help me
out of this wastebasket?

23:08.280 --> 23:09.076
Oh.

23:09.160 --> 23:10.832
- Oh, yeah.
- Now just pull.

23:10.920 --> 23:13.673
OK.

23:13.760 --> 23:16.035
- Harder.
- OK.

23:19.840 --> 23:23.594
So... listen. Can I ask you
a couple of questions now?

23:23.680 --> 23:26.513
No, no. Um... Not here.

23:26.600 --> 23:29.478
So busy. So much to do.

23:29.560 --> 23:32.313
Well, perhaps we could
have dinner tonight?

23:32.400 --> 23:35.517
Yes. Fine. Swell. See you then.

23:35.600 --> 23:38.273
I'll pick you up at your house.
It must be beautiful.

23:38.360 --> 23:40.316
- I'm sure it is.
- Hm?

23:40.400 --> 23:43.597
- I mean, sure it is!
- Yeah.

23:43.680 --> 23:46.956
So, where do you live?

23:47.040 --> 23:48.837
Um...

23:48.920 --> 23:51.115
Guess!

23:51.200 --> 23:53.430
Probably some highbrow street
somewhere.

23:53.520 --> 23:57.559
Highbrow Street, absolutely right.
Highbrow Street.

23:57.640 --> 24:02.350
How did you guess? Are you psychic?
But now, guess what number.

24:02.440 --> 24:05.637
I don't know. Number 17?

24:05.720 --> 24:07.915
Yes, all right. 17 Highbrow Street.

24:08.000 --> 24:10.719
OK. I'll pick you up at, shall we say...

24:10.800 --> 24:12.836
- eight o'clock?
- 5:30?

24:12.920 --> 24:14.751
- 4:15?
- 9:20?

24:14.840 --> 24:17.149
- Seven o'clock.
- OK. That was easy.

24:17.240 --> 24:18.992
- Yes, easy.
- OK, well I'll see you later.

24:19.080 --> 24:21.514
Yes. Eight o'clock.

24:21.600 --> 24:23.875
- Seven.
- Seven, seven.

24:25.200 --> 24:27.031
Well, um...

24:27.120 --> 24:30.078
- Goodbye.
- Yes.

24:30.160 --> 24:32.628
Adios, <i>mon chéri.</i>

24:35.000 --> 24:36.672
Much obliged.

24:36.760 --> 24:39.957
So, Kermit, tell me, what about
Lady Holiday? I mean, is she pretty?

24:40.040 --> 24:44.591
Oh, yeah. Not at all what I expected.
Nice eyes, sturdy legs.

24:44.680 --> 24:48.593
And it might have been my imagination,
but I think she found me attractive.

24:48.680 --> 24:50.159
Oh. Taxi!

24:50.240 --> 24:53.630
Well, of course she found you attractive.
It runs in the family.

24:53.720 --> 24:56.917
Taxi! Taxi!

24:57.000 --> 25:01.710
- I don't know why the cabs won't stop.
- Just leave it to me.

25:01.800 --> 25:04.189
Taxiiii!

25:07.960 --> 25:10.190
That's very effective.

25:10.280 --> 25:12.475
Yeah, it's great when it works.

25:12.560 --> 25:16.792
- Did you want me to stop or what?
- Thank you very much, sir.

25:16.880 --> 25:19.110
Oh, you can call me Beauregard.

25:19.200 --> 25:21.998
- Where are you guys going?
- The Happiness Hotel.

25:22.080 --> 25:25.470
Oh, good, that's where I'm going.
How do you get there?

25:25.560 --> 25:28.996
- Haven't you ever been there?
- Of course. I live there.

25:29.080 --> 25:31.071
I just don't know how to get there.

25:31.160 --> 25:34.277
- It's straight down this street.
- OK.

25:38.600 --> 25:42.513
- OK. Good. Now just keep going straight.
- Will do.

25:48.040 --> 25:50.679
It takes a while to get to know the town.

25:50.760 --> 25:53.957
- How long have you lived in London?
- All my life.

25:54.040 --> 25:55.792
How come you don't have
an English accent?

25:55.880 --> 25:58.519
Hey, I'm lucky to have a driver's license.

26:07.840 --> 26:10.832
- Hey, it's just up ahead there on the right.
- What is?

26:10.920 --> 26:13.912
- The Happiness Hotel.
- Oh, yeah.

26:14.000 --> 26:15.991
What's your room number?

26:16.080 --> 26:18.230
Wh? I don't know.
We're on the second floor.

26:18.320 --> 26:22.552
Oh, I'm sorry. I can only take you
as far as the lobby.

26:27.000 --> 26:29.560
Whee!

26:39.520 --> 26:42.080
You can never find a cab
when you need one.

26:42.160 --> 26:45.038
Whoo-whee!

26:45.120 --> 26:47.918
- Can we do that again?
- Well, thank you very much, Beauregard.

26:48.000 --> 26:50.150
You're welcome.
Hey, how do I get out of here?

26:50.240 --> 26:53.277
I suggest you make a U-turn.

26:53.360 --> 26:55.920
Right.

26:58.640 --> 27:01.712
- He's headed for the kitchen!
- Oh, no!

27:13.800 --> 27:17.156
Well, looks like steering wheel soufflé
for dinner.

27:17.240 --> 27:18.878
Again?

27:18.960 --> 27:20.951
If you'll excuse me, I'm going out to dinner.

27:21.040 --> 27:23.713
That's right. Kermit's got a date
with Lady Holiday.

27:23.800 --> 27:27.429
- You don't have to tell everybody.
- Oh. Right.

27:27.520 --> 27:30.478
Pops, don't tell anybody.
Kermit's got a date with Lady Holiday.

27:30.560 --> 27:32.949
Kermit's got a date
with Lady Holiday?

27:33.040 --> 27:35.952
Oh, wow. Wait till I tell
the guys in the band.

27:36.040 --> 27:38.998
- Tell us what?
- Yeah, what's going down?

27:41.720 --> 27:45.349
Kermit and Lady Holiday? All right!

27:49.640 --> 27:51.676
Fozzie, this is all very embarrassing.

27:51.760 --> 27:54.638
Kermit, don't worry.
It won't go outside this room.

27:55.080 --> 27:59.392
Here is a Muppet news flash.
Kermit the Frog to date Lady Holiday.

27:59.480 --> 28:02.074
Details at 11.

28:08.040 --> 28:10.270
Smile.

28:11.200 --> 28:13.919
Local poultry.

28:19.160 --> 28:22.118
Boy, it's a good thing you didn't
tell everybody where Lady Holiday lives

28:22.200 --> 28:24.270
otherwise they'd all
be camped on her doorstep.

28:24.360 --> 28:27.591
That is just for you and me to know,
brother.

28:27.680 --> 28:32.276
We are going to have ourselves
a time tonight. Wacka wacka.

28:32.360 --> 28:35.352
- "We"? What do you mean "we"?
- The two of us. You missed a spot.

28:35.440 --> 28:37.670
Anyway. When we get there tonight,
just act naturally.

28:37.760 --> 28:40.320
No, no. Wait a second, wait a second.
It's when <i>I get there.</i>

28:40.400 --> 28:45.679
This is my date with Lady Holiday.
I'm going alone. So it's "me" not "we".

28:45.760 --> 28:47.034
Oh.

28:47.120 --> 28:50.317
I see. Fine.

28:50.400 --> 28:52.755
Boy, I wish I had whiskers.

28:52.840 --> 28:54.876
Of course, then I'd have to use a blade.

28:54.960 --> 28:57.554
Kermit? Turn around.

28:57.640 --> 29:01.269
Are you really
going to go without me tonight?

29:01.360 --> 29:05.433
Well, Fozzie, I figure
this is something that I have to do alone.

29:06.840 --> 29:08.398
No problem.

29:08.480 --> 29:11.392
- Oh good. Just hand me my cuff links.
- Yes, sir.

29:11.480 --> 29:13.755
<i>And straighten my tie</i>

29:13.840 --> 29:17.515
<i>Just drench me in rich cologne</i>
<i>and don't ask me why</i>

29:18.520 --> 29:20.476
<i>Go on and pluck me a boutonniere</i>

29:20.560 --> 29:23.199
<i>You're moving up and walking on air</i>

29:23.280 --> 29:27.159
<i>Steppin' out with a star and feeling high</i>

29:28.120 --> 29:30.475
<i>Come polish my wing tips</i>

29:30.560 --> 29:33.154
<i>And call for the car</i>

29:33.560 --> 29:36.996
<i>I'll sweep her right off her feet</i>
<i>wherever we are</i>

29:38.280 --> 29:40.510
<i>A satin collar and velvet vest</i>

29:40.600 --> 29:42.830
<i>I never settle for second best</i>

29:42.920 --> 29:46.549
<i>Steppin' out with a star</i>
<i>Sad times. Bye-bye</i>

29:46.640 --> 29:49.074
<i>Have I got style?</i>

29:49.160 --> 29:51.549
<i>Have I got taste?</i>

29:52.680 --> 29:58.755
<i>On someone else. I swear.</i>
<i>This savoir-faire would be such a waste</i>

30:03.040 --> 30:05.508
- <i>Come toss me my top hat</i>
- Yes, sir!

30:05.600 --> 30:07.909
<i>I'm ready to fly</i>

30:08.000 --> 30:12.357
<i>Busting into the upper crust</i>
<i>as easy as pie</i>

30:12.760 --> 30:15.069
<i>Just watch my dreams come true</i>

30:15.160 --> 30:17.435
<i>This is something I was born to do</i>

30:17.520 --> 30:21.433
<i>Steppin' out with a star</i>
<i>That star is you</i>

30:42.640 --> 30:45.029
- <i>Have you got class?</i>
- <i>Have I got class?</i>

30:45.120 --> 30:47.395
- <i>Have you got chic?</i>
- <i>Have I got chic?</i>

30:47.480 --> 30:52.156
<i>To think that you and me</i>
<i>were nobody. Why. Only last week</i>

30:52.240 --> 30:53.992
Hey, guys!

30:59.240 --> 31:02.152
<i>I'm ready to flyyyyyy</i>

31:03.920 --> 31:07.071
- Kermit!
- At least I can try.

31:07.160 --> 31:09.515
<i>Just watch my dreams come true</i>

31:09.600 --> 31:11.830
<i>This is something I was born to do</i>

31:11.920 --> 31:14.354
<i>Steppin' out with a star</i>
<i>Bye. Bad times</i>

31:14.440 --> 31:16.749
<i>Steppin' out with a star</i>
<i>Hey. Good times</i>

31:16.840 --> 31:20.628
<i>Steppin' out with a star and feeling high</i>

31:23.360 --> 31:25.237
Yeah!

31:25.320 --> 31:27.595
Well, how do I look?

31:28.560 --> 31:30.755
Which one are you?

31:30.840 --> 31:33.035
- I'm the one on the right.
- Oh.

31:33.120 --> 31:36.908
Well, y... you look like you're gonna
have a terrific time.

31:37.000 --> 31:39.514
Without me.

31:39.600 --> 31:41.909
- Fozzie?
- What?

31:42.840 --> 31:45.195
You can come.

31:45.280 --> 31:47.032
- You mean it?
- Mm-hm.

31:47.120 --> 31:49.475
Oh, boy!

31:49.560 --> 31:52.393
Great news, gang. We can go!

32:36.080 --> 32:38.594
Awfully disappointing weather today.

32:38.680 --> 32:40.671
Hm?

32:40.760 --> 32:43.479
The weather. Awfully disappointing today.

32:43.560 --> 32:47.951
Is it, is it? Yes. Mm, yes, yes.
I know what you mean.

32:55.600 --> 32:58.273
It was rather disappointing yesterday.

32:58.360 --> 33:00.749
And the day before.

33:07.960 --> 33:10.633
What is it, Neville?

33:13.520 --> 33:15.590
Um...

33:16.800 --> 33:22.033
Pig... um... climbing up
the outside of the house, dear.

33:22.120 --> 33:23.155
Oh.

33:33.800 --> 33:36.951
Next time they want stunts
they get a double.

33:37.440 --> 33:39.635
The day before that
was awfully disappointing too.

33:39.720 --> 33:41.358
Mm.

33:41.440 --> 33:45.353
And of course the weekend was
perfectly frightful. Never stopped raining.

33:55.280 --> 33:57.840
- Neville?
- Hm?

33:57.920 --> 34:00.514
- Am I boring you?
- What, dear?

34:00.600 --> 34:05.230
- I said, am I boring you?
- Boring me?

34:05.320 --> 34:09.552
That's a good one.
I'm having the time of my life, dear.

34:09.639 --> 34:14.429
Neville, did you say... a <i>pig</i>
was climbing up the outside of the house?

34:16.840 --> 34:20.833
- Yes. Yes. Yes, I believe I did, yes.
- I thought so.

34:20.920 --> 34:23.717
You'd have to look a long way
to find a chap

34:23.800 --> 34:27.839
who was more... stimulated than I am, yes.

34:27.920 --> 34:30.592
Oh, dear me, no, no, no.

34:31.880 --> 34:36.556
The last time I was bored -
and never by you, my little armada...

34:36.639 --> 34:38.835
- What was that?
- Just making a point, dear.

34:38.920 --> 34:41.228
I mean, if I was bored I'd go out
and buy something, wouldn't I?

34:41.320 --> 34:44.995
Like cheese or quails' eggs.

34:45.080 --> 34:47.753
- Something like that.
- Yes, I suppose you would.

34:47.840 --> 34:53.072
Yes, of course I would, dear. That's
the sort of spur-of-the-moment fellow I am.

34:53.159 --> 34:55.196
What?

34:56.480 --> 35:00.189
- What, dear?
- What would you buy if you were bored?

35:01.000 --> 35:03.673
Ah! Uh...

35:06.360 --> 35:08.999
A jar of calf's-foot jelly?

35:12.440 --> 35:14.715
I'd like to come with you
and help you pick one out.

35:14.800 --> 35:17.872
Oh, that isn't necessary, Dorcas.
There's no need for you to leave the house.

35:17.960 --> 35:21.396
I wouldn't mind.
Haven't been outside for 12 years.

35:21.480 --> 35:23.914
Well, the weather's
been most disappointing.

35:24.000 --> 35:26.753
Still, there's no reason
for me to stay here all the time.

35:26.840 --> 35:28.990
The children are gone, the pets are dead,

35:29.080 --> 35:32.038
the butler's been discharged,
no one ever visits us.

35:45.720 --> 35:48.075
That was the doorbell, Neville.

35:49.000 --> 35:51.639
So it was.

35:51.720 --> 35:55.190
- And the butler's dead?
- No, no, no.

35:55.280 --> 35:59.034
The pets are dead.
The butler's been discharged.

35:59.120 --> 36:01.111
Ah.

36:02.960 --> 36:06.157
- I think one of us should answer it, Neville.
- Oh, do you?

36:06.800 --> 36:09.234
Or we could both answer it.

36:09.320 --> 36:12.312
Come, dear, I hardly think it's necessary
for both of us to...

36:12.400 --> 36:14.675
I'll answer it!

36:19.960 --> 36:21.996
I thought you said the pets were dead.

36:23.880 --> 36:26.189
- Hello.
- Uh...

36:26.280 --> 36:28.316
This is for you.

36:28.400 --> 36:31.949
Oh, thank you. Shall we go?

36:32.800 --> 36:37.555
You know, I've never been inside
a real ritzy English house before.

36:38.400 --> 36:42.188
- Aren't you hungry?
- Sure, but we've got a few minutes.

36:42.280 --> 36:44.919
OK. Let's take a few minutes.

36:46.520 --> 36:51.275
- Say, nice place you got here.
- Yes. I practically stole it.

36:52.240 --> 36:54.754
Let me show you around.

36:54.840 --> 36:58.833
- Who was that guy back there?
- Oh. Just some sort of servant.

36:58.920 --> 37:00.911
This, of course, is the drawing room.

37:01.000 --> 37:03.833
Did you decorate this place yourself?

37:04.800 --> 37:09.316
I'll just close the door.
It's very draughty.

37:10.480 --> 37:12.550
There's a chair and some walls.

37:12.640 --> 37:15.154
- A whirlwind tour, huh?
- Yes.

37:15.240 --> 37:18.630
This is the bedroom and, uh... bath.

37:19.600 --> 37:21.750
We have hot and cold running water.

37:21.840 --> 37:25.355
There's probably a bathtub and everything.

37:28.240 --> 37:32.313
Oh, here. I want to show you something.
This is the closet.

37:33.280 --> 37:35.555
Nice. Dark but nice.

37:42.000 --> 37:44.230
Ah. Sorry.

37:47.120 --> 37:52.911
Don't think me rude, but is there,
in fact, anything I can do for you at all?

37:54.600 --> 37:56.511
Um...

37:56.600 --> 37:59.558
Yes. Yes, yes.

37:59.640 --> 38:02.234
You may suggest a nice restaurant.

38:02.320 --> 38:04.709
Ah. Well, there's the Dubonnet Club.

38:04.800 --> 38:07.678
Actually that's not so much a restaurant,
