<i>Couldn't we ride?</i>

59:39.680 --> 59:42.558
Gangway! Watch it. Coming through.

59:42.640 --> 59:44.835
She's wonderful. She's so wonderful.

59:44.920 --> 59:47.992
She certainly seems to know
where she's going. It's time.

59:49.880 --> 59:52.348
All right, everybody.
Keep it moving. Don't linger.

59:52.440 --> 59:54.476
We just want to give them a hint,
a taste, a soupçon.

59:54.560 --> 59:56.357
Appetisers not four-course meals.

59:56.440 --> 59:58.874
Marie. I don't think we should chew gum.

59:59.520 --> 01:00:04.036
Stephanie, those false eyelashes are
coming unglued. Those shoes are scuffed.

01:00:04.120 --> 01:00:06.509
- I know where they are. I'll get them...
- Sorry.

01:00:06.600 --> 01:00:09.717
Watch it, buster. Oh. Mr Holiday, I'm sorry.

01:00:09.800 --> 01:00:11.677
Hello.

01:00:11.760 --> 01:00:12.988
- Miss...
- Piggy.

01:00:13.080 --> 01:00:14.229
- Miss Piggy?
- Right.

01:00:14.320 --> 01:00:16.276
Of course.

01:00:16.360 --> 01:00:19.238
Have dinner with me tonight.

01:00:19.320 --> 01:00:21.675
Mr Holiday, really, I'm very busy.

01:00:21.760 --> 01:00:24.479
- Could we meet just for a moment?
- Underwear, underwear, underwear.

01:00:24.560 --> 01:00:27.313
Just one brief moment, Miss Piggy. Miss...

01:00:27.400 --> 01:00:28.150
Hm?

01:00:28.240 --> 01:00:30.834
Miss Piggy.

01:00:30.920 --> 01:00:33.912
You're a very different-looking woman.

01:00:34.000 --> 01:00:37.276
I'm so tired of the same type.
Those tall, thin creatures

01:00:37.360 --> 01:00:40.591
with the long legs, the aquiline noses,

01:00:40.680 --> 01:00:44.150
the teeth like pearls, soft skin.

01:00:44.240 --> 01:00:47.755
Yeah, well, I can see why
that might make you sick to your stomach.

01:00:47.840 --> 01:00:49.637
- Please now... Please...
- Miss Piggy.

01:00:49.720 --> 01:00:52.632
No! Please! No. Please, please.

01:00:53.560 --> 01:00:56.916
Don't put a door between us.

01:00:57.880 --> 01:00:59.154
- Hi.
- Oh, Kermit.

01:00:59.240 --> 01:01:02.755
I was looking for the men's room.

01:01:02.840 --> 01:01:05.798
Kermit, I just want you to meet someone.
This is Nicky Holiday.

01:01:05.880 --> 01:01:08.838
Mr Holiday,
this is Kermit, my special friend.

01:01:09.520 --> 01:01:10.953
Oh.

01:01:12.160 --> 01:01:14.594
Nice to meet you.

01:01:14.680 --> 01:01:17.069
Well, excuse me.

01:01:19.120 --> 01:01:21.998
- Need I say more?
- He's a frog, isn't he?

01:01:22.760 --> 01:01:24.955
Yes.

01:01:27.480 --> 01:01:29.630
Miss Piggy.

01:01:30.640 --> 01:01:34.315
We could've had something
very, very special.

01:01:35.320 --> 01:01:38.596
Now, I can't be responsible
for what might happen.

01:01:38.680 --> 01:01:41.114
Yeah, well, uh...

01:01:41.200 --> 01:01:43.589
<i>C'est la vie.</i>

01:01:44.680 --> 01:01:46.989
I don't know why you love her like you do.

01:01:47.080 --> 01:01:50.390
I don't know why. I just do.

01:01:50.480 --> 01:01:52.516
Well, you'd better snap out of it, and fast.

01:01:52.600 --> 01:01:55.034
We've got to plant the goods on her
to take the heat off us.

01:01:55.120 --> 01:01:57.190
I know the plan.
I just wish there was another way.

01:01:57.280 --> 01:02:00.192
It's the only way. Especially now
the cops are starting to ask questions.

01:02:00.280 --> 01:02:03.909
OK, I'll do my job.
When I give the signal, you do yours.

01:02:04.000 --> 01:02:07.231
Forgive me, Miss Piggy.

01:02:09.080 --> 01:02:12.038
- Am I dressed right for this?
- You look fine, Fozzie.

01:02:12.120 --> 01:02:14.236
Thank you.

01:02:14.320 --> 01:02:17.835
And now,
without further ado,

01:02:17.920 --> 01:02:20.878
roses, hyacinths,

01:02:20.960 --> 01:02:24.032
lilacs and bluebells

01:02:24.120 --> 01:02:28.079
- make up our first fashion bouquet.
- Ooh!

01:02:28.760 --> 01:02:32.594
- Pretty nice lines, huh?
- Yes and the dresses aren't bad either.

01:02:32.680 --> 01:02:35.353
Here's capricious Carla,

01:02:35.440 --> 01:02:38.591
a dream in hyacinth-blue chiffon

01:02:38.680 --> 01:02:43.117
with the classic allure
of the white pleated collar and cuffs.

01:02:43.200 --> 01:02:45.475
The skirt, a flutter of godets,

01:02:45.560 --> 01:02:48.916
all complemented
by the cloudy folds of blue

01:02:49.000 --> 01:02:52.754
forming the perfect flower-framing hat.

01:02:52.840 --> 01:02:55.593
<i>Fantastique.</i> And thank you, Carla.

01:02:55.680 --> 01:02:59.389
- Pretty good-looking duds.
- I found the white pleated collar alluring,

01:02:59.480 --> 01:03:03.234
but I was rather taken aback
by the flutter of godets.

01:03:03.320 --> 01:03:04.639
Mm-hm.

01:03:05.600 --> 01:03:09.149
And now here's delicious Darla

01:03:09.240 --> 01:03:11.196
in a swirl of apricot silk

01:03:11.280 --> 01:03:15.034
above a tight bodice
with a cleverly-draped décolletage.

01:03:15.880 --> 01:03:21.000
Finishing with roses to match the
confection of flowers and silk on her head,

01:03:21.080 --> 01:03:24.038
forming a teeny-weeny hat.

01:03:29.760 --> 01:03:32.638
Oh. Ow! My knee. I think I've twisted it.

01:03:32.720 --> 01:03:34.950
You all right? You've got to get up!
You've got to go on!

01:03:35.040 --> 01:03:37.349
I can't go on!

01:03:37.440 --> 01:03:39.749
Oh! You poor thing.

01:03:39.840 --> 01:03:43.276
Oh, don't worry, Marla.
I'll stay right here with you.

01:03:43.360 --> 01:03:47.035
You can't. You've got to go on in her place.

01:03:49.960 --> 01:03:54.078
And now, the Lady Holiday
swimwear collection.

01:03:54.160 --> 01:03:57.436
Hey, Waldorf, wake up.
Here come the bikinis.

01:03:57.520 --> 01:04:00.193
Oh, boy. We'd better
synchronise our pacemakers.

01:04:00.280 --> 01:04:06.196
A cloud of lavender starburst pleating
surrounds our next model.

01:04:06.280 --> 01:04:09.192
Oh, I say!

01:05:04.640 --> 01:05:07.677
<i>A miracle of spring</i>

01:05:07.760 --> 01:05:10.832
<i>A miracle of beauty</i>

01:05:10.920 --> 01:05:16.916
<i>Be dazzled by the magic of one smile</i>

01:05:17.000 --> 01:05:19.958
<i>A vision of loveliness</i>

01:05:20.040 --> 01:05:22.315
<i>A universe of charms</i>

01:05:22.400 --> 01:05:27.918
<i>We'll never rest until you're in our arms</i>

01:05:36.440 --> 01:05:39.398
<i>Daffodils. Miss Piggy</i>

01:05:39.480 --> 01:05:42.836
<i>Whippoorwills. Miss Piggy</i>

01:05:42.920 --> 01:05:49.314
<i>Everything that's lovely.</i>
<i>Warm and spring. Miss Piggy</i>

01:05:49.400 --> 01:05:52.710
<i>Fantasy. Miss Piggy</i>

01:05:52.800 --> 01:05:55.917
<i>Ecstasy. Miss Piggy</i>

01:05:56.000 --> 01:05:58.798
<i>All that's fair or fine or wonderful</i>

01:05:58.880 --> 01:06:02.190
<i>Or anything. Miss Piggy</i>

01:06:02.280 --> 01:06:08.037
<i>Where does the rapture</i>
<i>begin and grow?</i>

01:06:08.120 --> 01:06:14.992
<i>Where does devotion and passion go?</i>

01:06:15.080 --> 01:06:18.356
<i>Happiness. Miss Piggy</i>

01:06:18.440 --> 01:06:21.716
<i>One caress. Miss Piggy</i>

01:06:21.800 --> 01:06:25.793
<i>All the world's ever wanted was you</i>

01:06:25.880 --> 01:06:28.633
<i>A dream come true</i>

01:06:28.720 --> 01:06:33.032
<i>Oh. Miss Piggy. It's you</i>

01:06:47.240 --> 01:06:53.634
<i>Where does the rapture</i>
<i>begin and grow?</i>

01:06:53.720 --> 01:06:59.636
<i>Where does devotion and passion go?</i>

01:07:00.600 --> 01:07:03.956
<i>Happiness. Miss Piggy</i>

01:07:04.040 --> 01:07:07.157
<i>One caress. Miss Piggy</i>

01:07:07.240 --> 01:07:11.358
<i>All the world's ever wanted was you</i>

01:07:11.440 --> 01:07:13.954
<i>A dream come true</i>

01:07:24.160 --> 01:07:28.278
<i>Oh. Miss Piggy. It's you</i>

01:07:28.360 --> 01:07:30.078
<i>It's you</i>

01:07:30.280 --> 01:07:33.397
<i>It's you</i>

01:07:48.680 --> 01:07:51.194
Oh, Miss Piggy, are you OK?

01:07:51.280 --> 01:07:55.910
Yeah, sure.
I was just looking for my contact lens.

01:08:03.120 --> 01:08:05.554
Excuse me. Excuse me.

01:08:05.640 --> 01:08:08.598
Oh, dear. Oh, you poor thing.

01:08:08.680 --> 01:08:11.240
Excuse me. Here, put this on.

01:08:11.320 --> 01:08:13.117
- You'll get a chill.
- Thank you very much.

01:08:13.200 --> 01:08:14.474
- You all right?
- I don't know what happened.

01:08:14.560 --> 01:08:16.630
I must've tripped.

01:08:16.720 --> 01:08:19.029
Wait a minute. What's this?

01:08:19.120 --> 01:08:22.590
I don't think these belong to me.

01:08:22.680 --> 01:08:25.069
Do you recognise this?

01:08:26.000 --> 01:08:29.072
That was my necklace.
But... where are the diamonds?

01:08:29.160 --> 01:08:33.038
- Where are the diamonds?
- Miss Piggy stole my necklace.

01:08:34.200 --> 01:08:37.795
- Miss Piggy, how could you?
- No! No! I don't know anything about it!

01:08:37.880 --> 01:08:41.077
Somebody must've put it... You!

01:08:41.160 --> 01:08:43.754
- It was you! Kermit was right there!
- Oh, no, no, no!

01:08:43.840 --> 01:08:46.354
You're a phoney! Yes you are.

01:08:46.439 --> 01:08:50.591
And you know what? You can't even sing!
Your voice was dubbed.

01:08:50.680 --> 01:08:53.274
Watch out, guys. Kermit!

01:08:53.359 --> 01:08:55.510
Don't worry, Miss Piggy.
We'll get you out of this.

01:08:55.600 --> 01:08:58.238
It just goes to show
you can't trust anybody.

01:08:58.319 --> 01:09:00.709
Excuse me, Lady Holiday,
will you be hiring any more pigs?

01:09:00.800 --> 01:09:03.598
Well, I shall certainly think twice about it.

01:09:03.680 --> 01:09:07.274
Kermit, find out if they'll let me
keep the costumes.

01:09:07.359 --> 01:09:10.113
What about your most famous piece of
jewellery, the fabulous Baseball Diamond?

01:09:10.200 --> 01:09:12.634
As from Monday,
the fabulous Baseball Diamond

01:09:12.720 --> 01:09:15.439
will go on permanent display
at the Mallory Gallery.

01:09:15.520 --> 01:09:19.798
I shall never have it either on my person
or in my possession again.

01:09:19.880 --> 01:09:21.598
That's right. It'll be in our possession.

01:09:21.680 --> 01:09:23.716
Tuesday at midnight
we'll go to the Mallory Gallery.

01:09:23.800 --> 01:09:26.633
The Baseball Diamond will be ours.

01:09:28.920 --> 01:09:31.559
<i>So there I was.</i>
<i>Backstage under a table.</i>

01:09:31.640 --> 01:09:35.189
I was doing a little photographic essay
on kneecaps,

01:09:35.279 --> 01:09:38.670
and I heard 'em planning to steal
the Baseball Diamond.

01:09:38.760 --> 01:09:39.749
Bummer.

01:09:39.840 --> 01:09:42.479
- So what's the plan, man?
- I already told you.

01:09:42.560 --> 01:09:46.678
Tuesday, midnight, at the Mallory Gallery.
That's all I know.

01:09:46.760 --> 01:09:48.876
You mean they're really gonna
try to steal the diamond?

01:09:56.920 --> 01:09:58.672
Quiet!

01:09:58.760 --> 01:10:01.035
"Look, Mother, it's my life, OK?"

01:10:01.120 --> 01:10:05.318
"So if I want to live on a beach
and walk around naked..."

01:10:05.400 --> 01:10:06.515
Oh.

01:10:06.600 --> 01:10:08.830
Now, if we wanna get
Miss Piggy out of jail,

01:10:08.920 --> 01:10:11.593
we're gonna have to catch
those thieves red-handed.

01:10:11.680 --> 01:10:12.556
Yes, Beau?

01:10:12.640 --> 01:10:16.189
What colour are their hands now?

01:10:16.280 --> 01:10:19.238
Now, we're about to embark
on a potentially dangerous mission.

01:10:19.320 --> 01:10:22.551
There could be physical violence,
there could be gunplay,

01:10:22.640 --> 01:10:25.154
and there's a slightest chance
that somebody might even get killed.

01:10:25.240 --> 01:10:28.391
So if anybody wants out,
now is the time to say it.

01:10:28.480 --> 01:10:30.072
- I'm out.
- Me too.

01:10:30.160 --> 01:10:31.673
- Ditto.
- Meep.

01:10:31.760 --> 01:10:34.957
Don't we have a gig around here,
or something or somewhere?

01:10:35.040 --> 01:10:37.634
Yeah, sorry. I got a dental appointment.

01:10:37.720 --> 01:10:39.915
It's like this, Kermit.
I have to go to work all day.

01:10:43.400 --> 01:10:45.960
Hold it!

01:10:47.360 --> 01:10:50.636
Shame on you.

01:10:51.560 --> 01:10:54.472
I thought we were in this thing together.

01:10:54.560 --> 01:10:58.997
I'm just as scared as you are,
but this has to be done.

01:10:59.880 --> 01:11:03.714
We don't want the bad guys to win.

01:11:03.800 --> 01:11:07.349
We've got to do this for... for... for justice.

01:11:07.440 --> 01:11:10.910
For... freedom. For... honesty.

01:11:13.040 --> 01:11:15.110
Boy, do I feel ashamed.

01:11:15.200 --> 01:11:17.919
Me too. I feel like two cents.

01:11:19.480 --> 01:11:21.914
- I'm back in.
- You can count on me.

01:11:22.000 --> 01:11:23.991
Oh, hey, I was only joking.

01:11:24.080 --> 01:11:27.311
Yeah, it'll be a lot of fun
to go out there and risk our lives.

01:11:27.400 --> 01:11:29.391
- Yeah!
- All for one and one for all.

01:11:29.480 --> 01:11:30.674
Yeah!

01:11:30.760 --> 01:11:35.231
At times like this
I am proud to be an American.

01:11:36.360 --> 01:11:39.193
Thank you. I knew I could count
on each and every one of you.

01:11:40.520 --> 01:11:42.511
Fozzie, are you OK?

01:11:42.600 --> 01:11:45.160
That took a lot out of me.

01:11:45.240 --> 01:11:48.277
OK. Now we don't have any time to waste,
so everybody gather round.

01:11:48.360 --> 01:11:51.158
And the first thing we have to do
is make our plans.

01:11:51.240 --> 01:11:52.992
- Right.
- Whoa!

01:11:54.720 --> 01:11:57.280
Or we could get some sleep.

01:12:12.640 --> 01:12:15.313
- Miss Piggy?
- What?

01:12:15.400 --> 01:12:17.755
Your lawyer is here to see you.

01:12:17.840 --> 01:12:20.479
Lawyer? I don't have a lawyer.

01:12:20.560 --> 01:12:23.358
Och, sure you do. Little green guy.

01:12:24.280 --> 01:12:29.798
Kermie! No wonder he hasn't come by
to see me. He had to finish law school.

01:12:40.160 --> 01:12:41.513
Oh, Kermit! Oh!

01:12:41.600 --> 01:12:44.319
Two minutes, pig.

01:12:44.400 --> 01:12:49.235
- Oh, Kermie. Oh, I've missed you so.
- Please. The name is Rosenthal.

01:12:49.920 --> 01:12:52.150
I'm your attorney.
That's the only way they'd let me in here.

01:12:52.240 --> 01:12:54.629
Oh, right.

01:12:54.720 --> 01:12:58.793
I've missed you so... Rosenthal.
It's been an eternity.

01:12:59.320 --> 01:13:03.757
- It's been 45 minutes.
- Time goes slow in the cooler.

01:13:03.840 --> 01:13:06.035
Well, I just want you to know
that we're gonna get you out of here,

01:13:06.120 --> 01:13:08.634
cos we're gonna catch those thieves
red-handed.

01:13:08.720 --> 01:13:11.280
What colour are their hands now?

01:13:11.360 --> 01:13:14.272
I don't think this is the time
for that type of humour.

01:13:14.360 --> 01:13:17.909
When you're in stir you take the laughs
when you can get 'em, Rosenthal.

01:13:18.000 --> 01:13:20.560
Yeah, well, anyway, just stay put

01:13:20.640 --> 01:13:23.234
because we've got a plan
and we're gonna prove you're innocent.

01:13:23.320 --> 01:13:26.710
You see, tomorrow night...
precisely at midnight,

01:13:26.800 --> 01:13:29.792
those thieves are gonna try to steal
Lady Holiday's Baseball Diamond

01:13:29.880 --> 01:13:31.233
from the Mallory Gallery.

01:13:31.320 --> 01:13:34.278
- And we're gonna stop 'em.
- Oh, Kermit, be careful.

01:13:34.360 --> 01:13:36.635
Don't worry
because I've got Gonzo and Fozzie

01:13:36.720 --> 01:13:39.951
and all our friends
from the Happiness Hotel to help.

01:13:40.040 --> 01:13:41.758
- Those clowns?
- Mm-hm.

01:13:41.840 --> 01:13:45.230
Great. I'll be stuck in the big house for life.

01:13:45.320 --> 01:13:48.118
"Big house"? Is that prison talk?

01:13:48.200 --> 01:13:53.672
Yeah, "big house", "squealer", "slammer".
That's the lingo we use here in the joint.

01:13:53.760 --> 01:13:56.433
Yeah. Well, you may talk tough,
Miss Piggy,

01:13:56.520 --> 01:14:00.638
but underneath I know you're still the same
beautiful, sensitive, vulnerable woman

01:14:00.720 --> 01:14:04.633
I was out with the other night.
The one who scarfed down all that caviar.

01:14:06.480 --> 01:14:08.869
You have such a way with words.

01:14:08.960 --> 01:14:11.235
I love you, Rosenthal.

01:14:24.920 --> 01:14:27.480
You're wearing my moustache.

01:14:29.720 --> 01:14:33.838
Yeah, well, you have mesh marks
on your face.

01:14:43.760 --> 01:14:45.637
- Glass cutter?
- Check.

01:14:45.720 --> 01:14:47.790
- Nylon rope?
- Check.

01:14:47.880 --> 01:14:50.599
- Computer deprogrammer?
- Check.

01:14:50.680 --> 01:14:52.511
- Stopwatch?
- Check.

01:14:52.600 --> 01:14:54.636
- Pocket laser?
- Check.

01:14:54.720 --> 01:14:57.280
- Infrared reflex?
- Check.

01:14:57.360 --> 01:14:58.873
- Portable detonator?
- Check.

01:14:59.360 --> 01:15:02.397
- Whoopee cushion?
- I think it's in the bus.

01:15:02.480 --> 01:15:05.711
- Rubber raft?
- It's got holes in it.

01:15:05.800 --> 01:15:08.997
Bag of chickens?

01:15:09.080 --> 01:15:12.311
- Fake vomit?
- It's on order.

01:15:12.400 --> 01:15:14.550
- Frisbee?
- Lost.

01:15:14.640 --> 01:15:16.358
- Pneumatic drill?
- Check.

01:15:16.440 --> 01:15:18.237
- Computer printout?
- Check.

01:15:18.320 --> 01:15:20.276
- Radar gun?
- Check.

01:15:20.360 --> 01:15:21.952
- Walkie-talkies?
- Check.

01:15:35.600 --> 01:15:38.672
- Wax lips?
- Man, I just had 'em.

01:15:38.760 --> 01:15:42.992
- Did you leave them in your other pants?
- I don't have no other pants.

01:15:43.080 --> 01:15:45.640
- Yo-yo?
- For sure.

01:15:45.720 --> 01:15:47.597
- Harpoon gun?
- That's you.

01:15:47.680 --> 01:15:50.194
Check.

01:15:50.280 --> 01:15:54.353
All right, team. Let's go for it.

01:15:54.440 --> 01:15:57.159
- Peanut butter?
- Animal ate it.

01:15:57.240 --> 01:16:00.357
Sorry.

01:16:00.440 --> 01:16:02.158
Well, Kermit,

01:16:02.240 --> 01:16:04.310
I guess that's it.

01:16:04.400 --> 01:16:06.630
All right, everybody.

01:16:06.720 --> 01:16:09.951
Let's go for it.

01:16:25.960 --> 01:16:27.996
Go for it!

01:17:38.080 --> 01:17:40.196
Beauregard.

01:17:40.280 --> 01:17:42.316
Back it up here.

01:17:43.640 --> 01:17:45.596
Sh. Sh.

01:17:45.680 --> 01:17:48.240
- OK. Quiet.
- Sh.

01:17:48.320 --> 01:17:51.232
OK. You guys
all got your disguises in place?

01:17:51.320 --> 01:17:52.958
Sh.

01:17:53.040 --> 01:17:55.235
Wow.

01:18:17.480 --> 01:18:20.392
- Wow!
- Sh!

