- I'm taking a picture.
- Sh.

01:18:22.560 --> 01:18:24.073
Rowlf, hand me the blowtorch.

01:18:24.160 --> 01:18:26.435
Blowtorch? Who said
anything about a blowtorch?

01:18:26.520 --> 01:18:29.159
I got some paper towels.

01:18:29.240 --> 01:18:31.754
How are we supposed to cut through
the bars if nobody brought stuff to cut with?

01:18:31.840 --> 01:18:35.196
I brought some hot mustard.
Maybe that'll eat through the bars.

01:18:35.280 --> 01:18:36.633
Eat through the bars!

01:18:36.720 --> 01:18:38.438
- Animal?
- What?

01:18:38.520 --> 01:18:42.559
Hey. Why don't you see if you
can eat through these iron bars.

01:18:42.640 --> 01:18:44.949
Eat through bars.

01:18:54.840 --> 01:18:57.434
- Doggy!
- The cops!

01:19:02.000 --> 01:19:05.879
Do you know where Lady Holiday's
Baseball Diamond is being kept?

01:19:06.440 --> 01:19:09.512
Funnily enough, I do.
It's at the Mallory Gallery,

01:19:09.600 --> 01:19:14.151
a virtually impregnable fortress,
many miles from here.

01:19:14.240 --> 01:19:18.028
- I only have a half an hour to get there.
- On foot? You'll never make it.

01:19:18.480 --> 01:19:21.950
- I know. How about a ride?
- You can read, I presume?

01:19:22.040 --> 01:19:24.190
"No passengers."

01:19:24.280 --> 01:19:27.875
Oh, couldn't you make an exception
for little old <i>moi?</i>

01:19:27.960 --> 01:19:30.599
Not even for little old <i>vous.</i>

01:19:30.680 --> 01:19:33.956
- Pretty please?
- No!

01:19:34.040 --> 01:19:36.554
I've tried to be nice.

01:19:37.000 --> 01:19:39.036
- Huh?
- Hiii-yah!

01:19:44.400 --> 01:19:45.913
Hey.

01:19:46.000 --> 01:19:49.390
- What's all the racket?
- What are you doing here?

01:19:49.480 --> 01:19:54.156
- A very brief cameo.
- Me too.

01:20:21.440 --> 01:20:23.476
Breaker one, this is Hamhock.
Do you read me?

01:20:23.560 --> 01:20:27.473
<i>Loud and clear. Hamhock.</i>
<i>This is Dirty Bird. What's your 20. over?</i>

01:20:27.560 --> 01:20:29.949
Well, good buddy,
we're westbound out of Highgate.

01:20:30.040 --> 01:20:32.156
Any smokies between me
and Blimeytown?

01:20:32.240 --> 01:20:34.913
<i>Negatory. Hamhock.</i>
<i>You're free and clear.</i>

01:20:35.000 --> 01:20:37.070
Ten-four, Dirty Bird. Much obliged.

01:20:37.160 --> 01:20:39.799
We got the hammer down and we gone.

01:20:41.720 --> 01:20:43.870
I never ordered no pepperoni.

01:20:43.960 --> 01:20:46.872
It's right here on the slip.
Medium pepperoni with double cheese.

01:20:46.960 --> 01:20:50.111
That's-a right. We don't-a
make them, we just-a deliver them.

01:20:50.200 --> 01:20:53.192
Somebody here called Pizza Twins,
and that's us.

01:20:53.280 --> 01:20:55.669
What's the name on that slip?

01:20:56.720 --> 01:20:58.915
Uh...

01:20:59.000 --> 01:21:01.560
- What's your name?
- Henderson.

01:21:02.480 --> 01:21:05.472
- That's it! That's the name on the slip.
- Ah!

01:21:06.680 --> 01:21:10.150
- But I hate pepperoni.
- I'll eat it.

01:21:10.240 --> 01:21:12.800
- Stand by, guys.
- Right!

01:21:15.880 --> 01:21:18.075
Ooh.

01:21:20.600 --> 01:21:22.636
'Ere. Just one moment.

01:21:23.560 --> 01:21:27.314
- Can I see that slip?
- Uh... uh... well...

01:21:28.240 --> 01:21:30.117
Actually, this is the wrong slip.

01:21:30.200 --> 01:21:33.033
That slip, sir,
you said it had my name on it.

01:21:33.120 --> 01:21:35.270
Oh, that-a slip.

01:21:35.360 --> 01:21:39.751
That-a slip we left at home.
But we got-a the pepperoni.

01:21:39.840 --> 01:21:42.400
- But I hate pepperoni.
- Hate pepperoni. Right.

01:21:42.480 --> 01:21:46.439
- How about you could feed it to the dogs?
- Yes. That's-a right. Here, sir.

01:21:46.520 --> 01:21:49.478
Oh, that's very thoughtful of you.
Thank you very much, sir.

01:22:03.680 --> 01:22:05.830
What am I? A glutton for punishment?

01:22:16.560 --> 01:22:18.755
- Hey, Fozzie...
- Sh.

01:22:18.840 --> 01:22:21.115
Fozzie, how do we get in?

01:22:21.200 --> 01:22:25.193
- Why don't we just ring the doorbell?
- No, no, no. There's got to be another way.

01:22:25.280 --> 01:22:29.751
Well, you'd better think of it pretty quick.
Those dogs have nearly finished the pizza.

01:22:29.840 --> 01:22:34.038
- I know. The roof.
- Oh, man. No way we'll ever get up there.

01:23:04.200 --> 01:23:07.237
Phew.

01:23:07.320 --> 01:23:11.598
- So far I'm not having any fun.
- Let me talk to 'em.

01:23:12.240 --> 01:23:14.515
Woof woof. Woof woof.

01:23:18.280 --> 01:23:20.999
It helps to know a second language.

01:23:22.840 --> 01:23:25.912
It's nearly midnight.
What am I going to do?

01:23:26.880 --> 01:23:28.871
Hey! Hey, you! Hey!

01:23:38.960 --> 01:23:41.349
What an unbelievable coincidence.

01:23:59.600 --> 01:24:02.319
Now, this window probably
has an alarm system on it.

01:24:02.400 --> 01:24:06.632
My assistant Beaker will check it out.
Go on, Beaker.

01:24:21.480 --> 01:24:24.438
Very good, Beaker. Now it's perfectly safe.

01:24:24.520 --> 01:24:27.910
Oh, good. Animal, do your stuff.

01:24:34.800 --> 01:24:36.438
Sorry.

01:24:46.360 --> 01:24:50.638
There it is.
The fabulous Baseball Diamond.

01:24:51.800 --> 01:24:53.313
How are we
gonna get down there?

01:24:53.400 --> 01:24:55.277
I suggest we jump.

01:24:55.360 --> 01:24:57.828
Are you crazy?
That's about a hundred feet.

01:24:57.920 --> 01:24:59.990
I didn't say it was a good suggestion.

01:25:00.080 --> 01:25:02.753
Maybe we could jump partway.

01:25:09.040 --> 01:25:10.871
Oh, boy, what do we do now?

01:25:10.960 --> 01:25:14.077
We're just gonna have to go down there
and catch those thieves red-handed.

01:25:14.160 --> 01:25:17.072
What colour are their hands now?

01:25:27.040 --> 01:25:31.158
We'll just have to improvise. We'll make
a ladder out of whatever will hold us.

01:25:31.240 --> 01:25:35.597
Good idea. Here's the paper towels.

01:25:36.720 --> 01:25:39.917
I'm coming, Kermie!

01:25:44.960 --> 01:25:47.349
Well, you wanted excitement.

01:26:39.720 --> 01:26:41.711
Excuse me, I don't think
that belongs to you.

01:26:47.200 --> 01:26:50.033
Say cheese!

01:26:51.400 --> 01:26:53.709
Woman!

01:26:53.800 --> 01:26:55.950
Hey, nice catch, Animal.

01:26:56.040 --> 01:26:58.873
- Heads up, Lew.
- Over here, Rowlf! Yeah, got it!

01:26:58.960 --> 01:27:01.838
Hot potato! Keep away. Here we go.

01:27:03.440 --> 01:27:06.079
I got it. Thank you. Be careful, guys.

01:27:06.160 --> 01:27:08.390
Catch it. Get him!

01:27:11.200 --> 01:27:12.315
Still got a good eye.

01:27:12.400 --> 01:27:15.631
Welcome to the wild world
of Muppet sports.

01:27:15.720 --> 01:27:18.075
This is Louis Kazagger
with a play-by-play

01:27:18.160 --> 01:27:19.309
- of the game.
- Woman!

01:27:19.400 --> 01:27:22.119
And it looks like ladies' night
here at the gallery.

01:27:22.200 --> 01:27:25.033
- Peekaboo.
- Hey! Ba-ba-do-be-bop.

01:27:25.120 --> 01:27:28.078
OK. Here she comes, boy!

01:27:35.400 --> 01:27:37.595
Hey, way to chuck,
way to look, way to move!

01:27:37.680 --> 01:27:42.071
Popcorn, popcorn.
Get your red-hot popcorn.

01:27:48.520 --> 01:27:50.272
Popcorn, chicken?

01:27:50.560 --> 01:27:52.755
Woman!

01:27:54.480 --> 01:27:57.278
- Woman!
- OK, OK.

01:27:57.360 --> 01:28:01.194
Lew Zealand leads off the order
as we join the game.

01:28:02.240 --> 01:28:05.710
- Chuck it to me, Beakie baby.
- Pitchy witchy, Beaker.

01:28:05.800 --> 01:28:08.109
Pitcher, you couldn't hit
the front side of a barn!

01:28:08.200 --> 01:28:10.395
Picture of the pitcher.

01:28:10.480 --> 01:28:12.471
Wait for what you want, Lew, baby.

01:28:12.560 --> 01:28:13.788
Rah, rah, rah!

01:28:13.880 --> 01:28:16.633
Beaker goes into the windup.

01:28:16.720 --> 01:28:20.633
It's the pitch.
It's a high fly ball to Kermit the Frog.

01:28:20.720 --> 01:28:23.075
I got it. I got it. I got it.

01:28:24.800 --> 01:28:27.519
Hey, gimme that diamond, you crook.

01:28:28.240 --> 01:28:30.800
- Come on, guys. Get him.
- All right. Back off!

01:28:33.400 --> 01:28:34.958
But, Nicky, why are you doing this?

01:28:35.040 --> 01:28:38.032
Why am I doing this?
Because I'm a villain. It's pure and simple.

01:28:38.120 --> 01:28:40.554
Excuse me, Mr Holiday, sir.

01:28:40.640 --> 01:28:43.837
Would you let Kermit go? If you hold him
too long he'll just give you warts.

01:28:43.920 --> 01:28:47.196
Oh, no. He's coming with us.
Come on, girls. Let's get out of here.

01:29:07.760 --> 01:29:08.795
Hii-yah!

01:29:09.040 --> 01:29:10.951
Hiii-yah!

01:29:13.880 --> 01:29:16.314
Hii-yah!

01:29:17.480 --> 01:29:19.948
- Hii-yah!
